The text centers on Leonardo Da Vinci, highlighted as a universal genius, artist, scientist, and philosopher. It discusses his artistic contributions, such as 'Vierge aux Rochers', 'Virgin of the Rocks', and 'The Virgin and Child with St. Anne and St. John'. Trained by Verrocchio, he also painted an angel in 'Baptism of Christ'. The narrative details his multifaceted skills in constructing, painting, and engineering, along with his role as a court-painter and his time in Florence around Easter 1500. Leonardo is noted for leaving his native land for France and is referenced consistently as an influential figure in various artistic and scientific endeavors.